\begin_layout Enumerate-Resume
We now have to create the part 2 of the algorithm: the computation of the
 jump frequency of all possible jumps.
 (Remark: in this random walk program, this part could be placed outside
 of the time loop since all jumps have the same frequency.
 However, we include it in the time loop to prepare the second part of the
 problem where we will have to compute the 
\begin_inset Formula $\varGamma_{XV}$
\end_inset

 according to the environment).
 In the program, we call 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{Gamma}$
\end_inset

 the vector such that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{Gamma}(i)$
\end_inset

 is the jump frequency of the exchange 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

.
 Use a 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

for
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 loop to compute the values of the different 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{Gamma}(i)$
\end_inset

 components.
 
\end_layout

